"a.整洁的，井然有序的 【英】 adj.整洁的，井然有 序的 (trim, tidy) 【考】 shipshape : disarray / squalid : cleanliness(反义：整齐对杂乱/ 肮脏对干净) 【记】 分割记忆：ship(船) ＋shape(形状)→船的 形状→整洁的 【例】 Everything was clean and shipshape. adj. 井然有序的(有秩序和清洁的) 【记】ship船, shape形状－船的形状－井然有序的 【参】shipwright(n 造船工人); wright(n 建造者) 【类】shipshape: disarray = squalid: cleanliness整齐的不是杂乱 = 肮脏的不是干净 【记】ship + shape 外形，象客轮一样整理得井然有序；shape + shape，有形，有形，真整洁，客人连连夸道 shipshape (adj.)  also ship-shape, ""properly arranged,"" 1640s, originally ""according to the fashion of a (sailing) ship,"" where neatness is a priority and the rigging must be serviceable and stowed properly; from ship (n.) + shape (n.)."
